President Obama issued a statement on the one-year anniversary of the death of Orlando Zapata Tamayo, a Cuban political activist. Zapata's death drew attention to the mistreatment of political prisoners in Cuba. The statement calls for the immediate and unconditional release of all political prisoners in Cuba and expresses solidarity with the Cuban people in their desire for freedom and justice. The statement also mentions the harassment and detention of Zapata's mother and others who sought to commemorate his death. President Obama reiterates the United States' commitment to defending the rights of the Cuban people.